tw.funnymph.commons.sort

Class PropertySortDescriptor<InputType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tw.funnymph.commons.sort.AbstractSortDescriptor<InputType>
      • tw.funnymph.commons.sort.PropertySortDescriptor<InputType>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SortDescriptor<InputType>, Transformer<InputType,Comparable<?>>

    public class PropertySortDescriptor<InputType>
extends AbstractSortDescriptor<InputType>
    This class provides an implementation that uses the given property name to obtain the comparable part from a object. The implementation uses the Java Reflection to call the getter method named get[PropertyName], e.g., getFirstName to get the first name of a person object. For the computed properties, the getter method can be customized by using the setGetterMethodPrefix(String) method.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pin-Ying Tu
